title: Moment a koala takes nap cuddling another koala at Symbio | Daily Mail Online
text: Share this article Share She looks around, twitching her fluffy ears before she rests her chin on Imogen's head and closes her eyes. Imogen appears to be asleep as well, with her had drooping downwards while she clings onto the branch. Symbio is an award-winning wildlife park on the outskirts of Sydney and home to a range of Australian and exotic animals. A sleepy koala named Willow (left) has been captured snuggling up to another koala named Imogen (right) and using her head as a soft pillow Willow was filmed cuddling up to Imogen at Symbio Wildlife Park in Helensburgh, New South Wales Share or comment on this article Most watched News videos
